This paper involves deep learning approaches to breast cancer detection in mammograms, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for data augmentation also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves medical imaging (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) which are also likely sub-categories.
